================================================================================
Modifications from upstream worklog-kb v1.1.0
================================================================================

This package (worklog-kb-grill) is a fork of worklog-kb v1.1.0, adding a
new `--grill` option to the `worklog log` command. The `--grill` flag runs an
interactive 3-round LLM-driven Q&A loop after classification and synthesizes
the answers into 4 retrospective sections (work record / notes / detailed notes
/ today's summary) of the daily log body.

All modifications are confined to the `dist/` directory:

  - dist/lib/llm.js         (refactored: providers return raw text; new
                             callLLMRaw export)
  - dist/lib/grill.js       (NEW: 3-round Q&A loop + SIGINT handler + prompts)
  - dist/lib/storage.js     (accepts optional bodyContent; generateCalloutsBody
                             renders the 4 retrospective blocks)
  - dist/lib/storage.d.ts   (synced type signatures)
  - dist/lib/grill.demo.js  (NEW: mock-based smoke test, not shipped as a CLI
                             entry point)
  - dist/commands/log.js    (new --grill option wiring grill → storage)

The original `worklog-kb` is published on npm and its declared upstream
repository URL (https://github.com/yangmeishux/worklog-cli) was unreachable at
the time of this fork; modifications were applied directly to the published
`dist/` artifacts. Source TypeScript is not included in this package.

Usage:

  npm install -g https://github.com/RandomXJJ/WorkGit.git
  worklog init
  worklog config --provider deepseek --key <your-api-key>
  worklog log --ai --grill "今天完成了 X 项目的整体梳理"